  "body": "# ðŸ’Ž Issue\r\n\r\n### Background\r\n\r\nRegarding saving blobs to the filesystem...\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nIf there's an error while saving, it will not delete the partial file. There might be a way to abuse this.\r\n\r\nI'm not exactly sure how this should be handled, but I think I'd do something like this:\r\n\r\n```diff\r\n--- a/beacon-chain/db/filesystem/blob.go\r\n+++ b/beacon-chain/db/filesystem/blob.go\r\n@@ -91,6 +91,13 @@ func (bs *BlobStorage) Save(sidecar blocks.VerifiedROBlob) error {\r\n                return err\r\n        }\r\n        partPath := fname.partPath()\r\n+\r\n+       // Ensure the partial file is deleted.\r\n+       defer func() {\r\n+               // Ignore return value, it's expected to return an error if the save is successful.\r\n+               _ = bs.fs.Remove(partPath)\r\n+       }()\r\n+\r\n        // Create a partial file and write the serialized data to it.\r\n        partialFile, err := bs.fs.Create(partPath)\r\n        if err != nil {\r\n```",
